cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO

The paper discusses an architecture for deep reinforcement learning, specifically for Atari games. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of random projection also suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO), as these fields often involve high-dimensional data and dimensionality reduction techniques.
